Description: Limestone ostracon: inventory of goods belonging to three persons, with remains of eleven lines of black-painted hieratic text on the recto and a further eight lines on the verso, some deleted by cross-lines, the text is faded in places.
Curator's comments: Bibliography: J.J Janssen, 'Commodity Prices in the Ramesside Period' (Leiden, 1975), p.28-9.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (136369) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/136369)
